==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mollemoke
<hw>Mol"le*moke`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sw.
<ets>mallemucke</ets> the stormy petrel.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any one of several species of large pelagic petrels and fulmars, as
<spn>Fulmarus glacialis</spn>, of the North Atlantic, and several
species of <gen>Aestrelata</gen>, of the Southern Ocean. See
<er>Fulmar</er>.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>mollymawk</asp>,
<asp>malmock</asp>, <asp>mollemock</asp>, <asp>mallemocke</asp>,
etc.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mollient</ent>⟦br⟧
